# Checklist

## Create a Module

. create prisma model first (if needed)
. create the folder with respective name in the modules folder
. create types for the module, notice that if its gonna extend any other module | `schema.graphql`
. pull related enums from prisma if any exists | `enums.graphql`
. create validation for the module if needed | `inspector.ts`
. add the inspector object to /src/library/inspectors.ts
. create the controller for that module if needed | `controller.ts`
. add the controller class to /src/library/controllers.ts
. create resolver if needed | `resolver.ts`
. create module object in the index.ts | `index.ts`
. add the service to `aliases` export
. add this model's database reset function to /tests/helpers/reset-db.ts
. write tests

-final folder structure :

```bash
   [module-name]/
   ┣ enums.graphql
   ┣ index.ts
   ┣ resolvers.ts
   ┣ controller.ts
   ┣ schema.graphql
   ┗ inspector.ts
```
